During National Ovarian Cancer Awareness Month, Melania and President Trump express their condolences for those who have lost loved ones to ovarian cancer. They emphasize the importance of supporting women battling this disease and highlight that early diagnosis and treatment can significantly improve survival rates. The National Cancer Institute estimates that 22,000 Americans will be diagnosed with ovarian cancer in 2017, with approximately 14,000 losing their battle. The Trump Administration is committed to preventing, treating, and defeating ovarian cancer through innovative research and medical breakthroughs. They also mention the approval of two maintenance therapies for ovarian cancer by the FDA this year. Melania and President Trump encourage Americans to educate themselves about ovarian cancer and support efforts to create a healthier future for everyone.